# Reliability & Error Handling

## Never swallow errors silently

```js
// BAD
} catch { /* ignore */ }

// GOOD — degrade with telemetry
} catch (err) {
  ErrorReporter.capture('save_load_failed', err);
  return structuredClone(DEFAULT_SAVE);
}
```

## Bounded iteration

Every gameplay loop must respect documented caps (`MAX_ENEMIES`, `ENEMY_DESPAWN_BATCH`). New `while` loops need a max iteration comment.

## Assertions vs validation

- **Assert** — impossible if code is correct (pool index, apply upgrade twice).
- **Validate** — external input (settings id, character id) — return fallback.

## User-visible recovery

Combat/UI failures: toast or modal, unstick `paused` / `modalPause`. Never leave player soft-locked.

## Resource cleanup

On enemy/projectile removal: `geometry.dispose()`, `material.dispose()` when not shared.

## Global errors

Gameplay entry must register `error` and `unhandledrejection` handlers that log structured context (game mode, version).
